Use to be a go to of mine but the last couple months the quality of the food here has nosedived. My past 2 orders have had issues and when i called this last time the guy just wanted to argue with me (first time it was completely wrong but at least they replaced it). I order the hummus with lamb at least 70% of the time, and this latest order came swimming in grease. It was basically a watery mess when I opened the box. It also spilled out of the bag and box all over my table and I had to clean it up. I tried to take a bite but it was disgusting. I called and they only wanted to argue that it was spicy sauce. I asked for it on the side first off (and i usually get some in a cup), but that one bite wasn’t spicy at all. I can tell the difference between grease and spicy sauce as I think most people in the world could too. Other times I’ve ordered the lamb had been goning downhill too, so I had been doing more kebabs lately which are ok. Eventually I just hung up as we were getting nowhere, my wife and I will not be going back. So sad, this place used to be so good.

I called in for to go order but later changed my mind and ate there. Also ordered Turkish coffee which was authentic and delicious. I am not sure if they sever halal meat but one employee verbally confirmed the meat to be halal. Would love to see if they have a certificate from their halal meat supplier. Parking could be an issue if you visit in peak hours. But do give them a visit if you are in town. I will definitely be coming back.

I will never go back and will be sure to advise anyone thinking of going to stay away.

There is not enough stars to give to this restaurant.  My first to Mona's Cafe was in 2009 and it was like love at first meal.  Boy o boy, I just can't get enough of this place.  This is how good this place is to me, I drive all the way from Memphis, TN to eat at this place.  When I am in New Orleans, this is the only place I eat.  I have not tried any other restaurant in New Orleans but this place.  I eat Mona's Cafe at break, lunch, and dinner while in New Orleans.  The falafels are to die for, the kibby is out this world, grape leaves spectacular, the masabaha superb, tea is insane, and the lebana calls my name.  I try to come every year.  This year I drove there just for the weekend to eat here and it felt like the same experience I had at first but better.  While eating my meal, I am almost for certain this is the best Arabic Food you will ever taste, at lease in the U.S. I've been to many cities and tried their Arabic Food to see if they would top Mona's Cafe but Mona's Cafe has mastered the creation of spices mixtures and fine cuisines.
